                            <comment id="16576180" author="paulk" created="Fri, 10 Aug 2018 12:01:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for reporting the issue. I have changed the util CliBuilder to follow the same behavior as before.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you ever switch to the picocli version of CliBuilder you will notice a difference in behavior. It has a few more options for handling unknown option-like parameters. We can possibly add an asBoolean method to the picocli OptionAccessor. Then if you use groovy truth to check that things went well you should get the closest possible equivalent to the current behavior.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16586711" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Tue, 21 Aug 2018 00:38:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FYI I fixed the picocli CliBuilder so it behaves the same as the commons-cli CliBuilder.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
